# =============================================================================
# card-ops .gitignore
# =============================================================================
# PRINCIPLE: The repo ships the SYSTEM (modes, scripts, templates, config
# examples). It NEVER ships USER DATA (statements, profiles, reports, tracker
# entries). When in doubt, exclude it -- a missing .gitignore line can leak
# financial data; a surplus line just means you re-create a file locally.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. FINANCIAL DOCUMENTS -- the nuclear exclusion zone
#    Every statement format that any bank, brokerage, or aggregator exports.
#    Applied globally so they're caught no matter where someone drops them.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.pdf
*.PDF
*.ofx
*.OFX
*.qfx
*.QFX
*.qif
*.QIF
*.qbo
*.QBO
*.iif
*.IIF

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. USER DATA LAYER (per CLAUDE.md data contract)
#    These directories hold personal financial information at runtime.
#    Only .gitkeep and example/template files survive.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Statements -- the entire directory, all formats, no exceptions
statements/

# Reports -- personalized evaluations with credit scores, income, card details
reports/

# User profile (real financials) -- example is safe, actual profile is not
config/profile.yml
config/profile.yaml
config/profile.*.yml
config/profile-*.yml
!config/profile.example.yml

# User mode overrides -- personal preferences, issuer notes
modes/_profile.md

# Card tracker and pipeline -- your actual portfolio and pending offers
data/cards.md
data/pipeline.md
data/cards.md.bak
data/*.bak

# Batch working files -- contain evaluation scores and personal card data
batch/tracker-additions/*.tsv
batch/tracker-additions/merged/
batch/logs/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. COMMON SPREADSHEET / DATA EXPORTS
#    People export bank data to these formats. Block them globally.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.xlsm
*.xlsb
*.csv
*.tsv

# Allowlist: specific TSVs that are system templates, not user data
# (none currently -- tracker-additions TSVs are user data)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3b. PERSONAL ANALYSIS SCRIPTS
#     User-created scripts that parse personal transactions, reference
#     specific cards, or contain spending amounts. System scripts are
#     in the root as *.mjs -- personal analysis goes here.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*_analysis.py
*_analysis.r
*_analysis.R

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. ITERATION / LOOP ARTIFACTS
#    Research loop logs are large and session-specific, not part of the system.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
iteration_log.md
improvement_report.md

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. ENVIRONMENT AND SECRETS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.cer
credentials.*
secrets.*
token.*

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. OS AND EDITOR
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db
ehthumbs_vista.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. NODE / RUNTIME
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
package-lock.json
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. SAFETY NET -- catch common accident patterns
#    Someone renames a statement, drags in a screenshot of their credit score,
#    or pastes exported data into a text file in the wrong directory.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Image formats (screenshots of statements, credit scores, approvals)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.bmp
*.tiff
*.heic
*.webp

# Archive formats (zipped statement bundles)
*.zip
*.tar
*.gz
*.7z
*.rar

# Database files (parsed statement caches)
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. PYTHON ARTIFACTS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 10. DERIVED DATA (v2 architecture)
#     Transaction parquet files and analysis outputs are generated locally.
#     Config files (config/*.yml) and market cache (data/market/*.yml) are
#     curated data and should NOT be gitignored.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
data/transactions/*.parquet
data/analysis/*.yml
